requirements: Write a script that uses numpy to compute the eigenvalues of a given 3x3 matrix and prints them.

test_cases.name: test_standard_matrix
test_cases.description: Functional test using a standard 3x3 matrix to ensure correct eigenvalue computation.

test_cases.name: test_symmetric_matrix
test_cases.description: Test a symmetric matrix, verifying that real eigenvalues are correctly handled.

test_cases.name: test_identity_matrix
test_cases.description: Edge case testing the identity matrix where all eigenvalues are 1.

test_cases.name: test_complex_eigenvalues
test_cases.description: Test a matrix known to produce complex eigenvalues, ensuring NumPy handles complex output.

test_cases.name: test_zero_matrix
test_cases.description: Boundary condition test using a matrix of all zeros.

test_cases.name: test_invalid_dimensions
test_cases.description: Error handling test: Input matrix is 4x4 (non-3x3). Should raise ValueError.

test_cases.name: test_non_numeric_input
test_cases.description: Error handling test: Input matrix contains a non-numeric string. Should raise ValueError during conversion.

recommendations: The implementation is robust and correctly uses NumPy's `linalg.eigvals`. Error handling for dimension mismatch and non-numeric input is effective.
For production use, consider adding type hints to the function signature (`matrix_data: list[list[float]]`) for better maintainability.
